# TypeScript Standards

## Types Over Any

- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` and narrow, or define proper types.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions/intersections.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
function process(data: any) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
interface ScanResult {
  redFlags: string[];
  identifier: string;
}
function process(data: ScanResult) { ... }
```

## Null Safety

- Use optional chaining (`?.`) and nullish coalescing (`??`).
- Prefer `T | null` over `T | undefined` when the absence has meaning.

## Async

- Always `await` or `.then()`; never leave promises unhandled.
- Use `async/await` over raw `.then()` chains for readability.

## Exports

- Export types with `export type` for better tree-shaking.
- Use barrel files (`index.ts`) sparingly; prefer direct imports.

## Strict Mode

- Keep `strict: true` in tsconfig.
- Fix type errors; do not use `@ts-ignore` without a comment explaining why.
